{
  "text": "Although the spring loaded preformed silos have many advantages, but we believe that they can make the diameter of the defect larger There have been various methods reported to deal with closure of a large or complex gastroschisis. These include prosthetic materials such as sugisis [CITATION_1] , gortex [CITATION_2] , silastic silo [CITATION_3] and autologous materials such as umbilical cord [CITATION_4] , dura, musculo-cutaneous flaps and meshed skin grafts [CITATION_5] reported.",
